  "title": "Ability to Provide sortBy compareFunction along with defaults",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nFeature\r\n\r\n**Feature: What is your use case for such a feature?**\r\nYou might want to have a compare function that also still respects the `isRefined` setting for sortBy.\r\n\r\n**Feature: What is your proposed API entry? The new option to add? What is the behavior?**\r\nWe could provide the ability to define a compareFunction, and [the various possible values](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets/refinementList.html#struct-RefinementListWidgetOptions-sortBy) provided as an object or otherwise: sortBy`[Array<string>|object{defaults: Array<string>, compareFunction: function}]`.\r\n\r\nPotential way to define (not entirely sure the best way to approach):\r\n```js\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\r\n    container: document.querySelector(\"#brand\"),\r\n    attributeName: \"brand\",\r\n    sortBy: {\r\n        defaults: ['isRefined', 'name:asc', 'count:desc'],\r\n        compareFunction: (a, b) => {\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n  })\r\n);\r\n```",
